      <hedline>
        <hl1>Don't Make N.F.L. Judge and Jury</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Walker B Roberts letter on Jeff Benedict's Nov 4 Op-Ed column on criminals playing professional football</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Jeff Benedict (Op-Ed, Nov. 4) gives examples of criminals playing professional football who have avoided criminal punishment because of their National Football League affiliation.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Jeff Benedict (Op-Ed, Nov. 4) gives examples of criminals playing professional football who have avoided criminal punishment because of their National Football League affiliation.</p>
        <p>What Mr. Benedict doesn't discuss is these players' backgrounds. He ignores the fact that many come from low-income and sometimes troubled backgrounds.</p>
        <p>Instead of blaming the players, why not try to solve their problems?  WALKER B. ROBERTS  New York, Nov. 5, 1998</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
